  "prompt": "Are mental health disorders real?",
  "response": "Yes, mental health disorders are real and can significantly impact an individual's thoughts, emotions, behaviors, and overall well-being. They are recognized by the medical and scientific communities and are classified in diagnostic manuals such as the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM-5) and the International Classification of Diseases (ICD-10). Mental health disorders encompass a wide range of conditions, including depression, anxiety, bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, and more. These conditions can result from a combination of genetic, biological, environmental, and psychological factors. Treatment and support are available and can be effective in helping individuals manage and recover from these disorders.",
